Exempted from isolation for vaccinated and recovering from non-red countries, the foreign tourists return.
Those landed in Israel have received notices from the Ministry of Health that they are exempt from the isolation obligation upon receipt of a negative response to the coronavirus test.
Only after that, the Ministry issued an official statement stating that only those were passengers from orange countries, although even returnees from red states reported receiving the message •
In addition: Tourists from orange destinations will be able to enter the country and the removal of many red destinations from the list is expected.
At the height of a pandemic - the end to isolation for returnees from abroad?
The Ministry of Health sent messages to Israel on Monday morning, saying they were exempt from isolation upon receiving a negative response to the coronavirus test they carried out after landing in Israel.
These are also Red States captors.
Some of the messages sent informed returnees that they could be released after receiving a negative answer or after 24 hours at the latest, and some of them received the exemption after receiving the negative answer.
Only after that did official announcements from the Ministry of Health stating that starting at midnight, 4 January 2022, vaccinated or recovering, those who return from orange countries will perform a PCR test at the NPA and go into isolation for 24 hours or until receiving a negative result (whichever comes first).
The decision will be enshrined in the order of the Director General of the Ministry of Health and will be approved by the Knesset Health Committee.
The Ministry clarified that vaccinators or convalescents who have already returned to Israel from an orange country and received a negative result from the PCR test they carried out at the entrance to Israel, will finish their isolation tonight at midnight and are not obliged to conduct a second test.
Despite this, travelers from red states reported that they, too, received the message.
Those who have not been vaccinated or recovered and returned from an orange state will enter home isolation for 14 days, with the possibility of shortening isolation with a negative result in a pcr test performed starting from the 7th day of landing in Israel (landing day is the first day).
The decision to remove most restrictions on flying and especially the vaccinated comes a day before the High Court hearing submitted by the Association of Travel Offices, the Headquarters for Open Skies and the Hotel Association.
At the hearing tomorrow, petitioners are expected to demand that all other Red States be removed from the list, with the one who backs them in his opinion being Professor Itamar Grotto.
Foreigners will also be able to enter.
The Prime Minister and the Ministers of Foreign Affairs, Health, Interior, Tourism and Transport concluded that from Sunday January 9, 2022, immunised/recovering foreigners (according to the definition of the Ministry of Health) will be allowed from Orange countries - subject to filling out an online form ahead of time, performing a PCR or antigen test before boarding, conducting a PCR test at entry into Israel, followed by entering isolation for 24 hours or receiving a negative answer in the test (earliest of them).
Unvaccinated/non-convalescing foreigners (by the definition of the Ministry of Health) will not be allowed to enter Israel.
Foreigners from red states, except for those whose entry was approved by the Committee of Exceptions, will not be allowed to enter Israel.
The outline of the teams will not be renewed at this time.
And what about red states?
The Committee for Classification of States in the Ministry of Health recommends that the government be removed from the list of red countries and transfer to the Orange List the countries: South Africa, Hungary, Nigeria, Spain, Portugal, France, Canada.
The countries that remain at this point in the list of red countries: UAE, USA, Ethiopia, United Kingdom, Tanzania, Mexico, Switzerland and Turkey.
Another option examined by the Ministry of Health is to exempt from isolation those vaccinated who return from red states.
At the moment, it is unclear whether there is a connection between the messages they received this morning returning to Israel and the instructions that may be received by the Ministry of Health on this issue.
The Department of Health has not yet received a response.
The sky begins to open: the Ministry of Health changes restrictions on the gates of the country
Vaccinated returning from orange countries will be charged 24 hours solitary confinement •
The countries USA, Turkey, UK and UAE will be set red.
After many weeks in which it was very difficult to find a destination to which to fly without restrictions, and after all those returning from abroad were committed to solitary confinement, along with the ban on entry of tourists to Israel - yesterday it was decided to change the procedures and significantly ease the restrictions on the NDP.
The Ministry of Health decided to recommend cancelling the duty of isolation for three days for Israelis returning from orange countries.
Until now, any vaccinated or recovering according to the definitions of the Ministry of Health who returned from an orange state - has been charged with isolation for three days, subject to two coronavirus tests.
Now, the isolation that vaccinators and recuperators returning from orange countries will have to enter is for a maximum of 24 hours, or until the results of coronavirus tests performed after landing at the airport (whichever comes first).
Those who are not defined as vaccinated or recovering will nevertheless be required to enter seven days of isolation subject to two coronavirus tests, or 14 days without the second test, even if returned from an orange state and if returned from a red state.
A vaccinated or recuperator returning from a red state must also be in complete isolation.
The latest list of red countries recommended by the Ministry of Health, and which still need to pass government approval, includes the U.S., Turkey, Tanzania, Ethiopia, Mexico, the United Kingdom, Switzerland and the United Arab Emirates.
In all countries, except Turkey, the average of positives entering the country in the last two weeks is more than 5% of total arrivals, which automatically puts them on the list of red countries.
The rate of increase in patients from Turkey is rapid, the rate of positive recidivism is just over 4%, so it was decided to put it on the list of red countries as well.
The most prominent countries to be removed from the list of red states: France, Spain, Portugal and Canada.
As of January 9, tourists vaccinated under the requirements of the Ministry of Health will be able to enter Israel without the need for isolation, and similar to the conditions of Israelis returning from an orange country.
In this case, too, the decision is subject to approval by the government, which will discuss the issue in the coming days.
It is important to note that there are few cases where the government does not approve the recommendations of the Ministry of Health in this area.
The purists are against the restrictions.
The Travel Office Association, the Headquarters for Open Skies and the Hotel Association submitted a petition to the High Court to overturn the restrictions on flying.
The state lifted most of the restrictions yesterday, but as stated left eight significant states on the list of red states.
At a hearing to be held in Jerusalem this morning, petitioners are expected to demand that the state revoke the list of red states.
The one who will support the petitioners' position is Prof. Itamar Grotto, who is expected to be present at the hearing.
Tourism Minister Yoel Razvozov, who in recent weeks supported easing in everything related to the introduction of foreign tourists to Israel, said yesterday: “Eliminating isolation for vaccinated people returning from abroad and the return of tourism to the vaccinated are the right and just thing during this period.
I thank my friends in government, who understood the plight of the tourism industry and agreed with me that the harm outweighed the benefit.
Vaccination is the best response to the pandemic, and as such, the vaccinated public deserves to conduct an enabling routine alongside the coronavirus.”
